    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>I found GIMP 2.8 useful for the following workflow tasks that typical photographers will want:</p>

<ul>
<li>Contrast mask</li>
<li>Image sharpening (using <em>&lt;Image>-Filters-Enhance-Sharpen</em> or <em>&lt;Image>-Filters-Enhance-Unsharp mask</em>)</li>
<li>Smart sharpening (when you don&rsquo;t want that silly look that comes from sharpening everything)</li>
<li>Color balancing</li>
<li>Correcting muddy pictures (auto levels)</li>
<li>Correcting blemishes (scratches and other artifacts)</li>
</ul>

]]></content>
